note.ab:
Theo writes that Weissenbruch is not dead, because Van Gogh had assumed this in letter 776. Tersteeg sent the following eight watercolours by Weissenbruch, which had been purchased on 30 August 1889 by Goupil’s Hague branch: 
                            Route & canal
                         (Road and canal); 
                            Canal, effet de nuage
                         (Canal, cloudy effect); 
                            Paysage & mare
                         (Landscape and pond); 
                            Mare
                         (Pond); 
                            Moulins, effet de soir
                         (Windmills, evening effect); 
                            L’heure de traire
                         (Milking time); 
                            A travers des champs
                         (Across the fields) and 
                            Ferme, praire & eau
                         (Farmhouse, meadow and water). The first two were sold the same month to a collector; the others remained in Paris or were sent to the branches in London and New York. (RKD, Goupil Ledgers, nos. B&V 14237-14244).
